OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F423A1778061972
OL,3,CWilliam brings cakes as hill farmers
OL,4,Cshare challenges of diversifying
OL,6,FMr Hunter invited neighbours Philip
OL,7,FMetcalfe, 53, and his son James, 23,
OL,8,Fwho run Usha Gap Farm and have opened
OL,9,Fa campsite, and Michael and Hannah
OL,10,FWaggett, both 36, who have nearby
OL,11,FSatron Farm.
OL,13,FWhile the host made teas and coffees
OL,14,Ffrom the back of his all-terrain
OL,15,Fvehicle parked in his yard, William
OL,16,Fhanded over a box of cakes bought from
OL,17,Fa local bike stop, including a brownie
OL,18,Fand a Twix cake, which he later called
OL,19,Fa "calorie grenade".
OL,26,@{D@COU{D@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/7
