PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F423A1778061972
OL,3,CWilliam brings cakes as hill farmers
OL,4,Cshare challenges of diversifying
OL,6,FWilliam asked the farmers about the
OL,7,F"headwinds" they faced in the
OL,8,Findustry, which has been hit by rising
OL,9,Ffuel costs.
OL,11,FMr Hunter described diversifying the
OL,12,Fbusiness by opening the bunkhouse
OL,13,Fwhile still looking after livestock,
OL,14,Fsaying: "We are doing the farming,
OL,15,Fmaking beds and cleaning toilets, we
OL,16,Fare doing everything."
OL,18,FHe told William a strength of
OL,19,FSwaledale was the close-knit community
OL,20,Fwhere neighbours worked together.
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@KO]vD@IOUxD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/7
